# Card_Moba — AI Coding Rules & Context Map

## 1. High-Level Overview

### 1.1 Project Description
3v3 synchronous turn-based card MOBA game. Core mechanics: 1+2 fixed lane assignment, Instant-Plan dual-track card system, Central Tower PVE+Boss fights, lane-collapse 3v3 final battle, 25-round hard cap.

### 1.2 Monorepo Architecture
```
Card_Moba/                          ← Git root
├── Client/                         ← Unity 2022.3 LTS project root
│   ├── Assets/Scripts/             ← Client C# code (4-layer architecture)
│   │   ├── Presentation/           ← View layer (UI, VFX, Audio, Input, Scene)
│   │   ├── GameLogic/              ← Business logic (RoundFlow, CardSystem, PlayerState, TeamComm)
│   │   ├── Data/                   ← Data layer (ConfigData, PlayerData, BattleCache)
│   │   ├── Network/                ← Network layer (Connection, MessageDispatch, Security, Proto)
│   │   ├── Common/                 ← Shared utilities (Constants, Utils, Extensions, Events)
│   │   └── Editor/                 ← Editor-only tools (CardEditor, BattleSimulator)
│   ├── Assets/Resources/Prefabs/   ← Runtime prefabs (Cards, Characters, UI, VFX, Scene)
│   ├── Assets/ScriptableObjects/   ← SO data files (Cards, Heroes, GameConfig)
│   ├── Assets/StreamingAssets/Config/ ← Hot-update config JSONs
│   └── Packages/manifest.json      ← UPM manifest (includes Shared as local package)
│
├── Shared/                         ← UPM local package (com.cardmoba.shared v0.1.0)
│   ├── BattleCore/                 ← Authoritative settlement engine (noEngineReferences!)
│   │   ├── CardEffects/            ← Card effect components & pipeline
│   │   ├── Context/                ← Battle context (all mutable game state)
│   │   ├── Random/                 ← Seeded PRNG for deterministic settlement
│   │   ├── RoundStateMachine/      ← 7-phase round FSM
│   │   └── Settlement/             ← Settlement priority engine
│   ├── Protocol/                   ← Communication protocol (Enums, Messages)
│   └── ConfigModels/               ← Data models (Card, Hero, Relic, Rule)
│
├── Server/                         ← ASP.NET Core backend
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── CardMoba.Gateway/       ← SignalR WebSocket gateway
│   │   ├── CardMoba.AccountService/
│   │   ├── CardMoba.MatchService/
│   │   ├── CardMoba.RoomService/   ← Core game room lifecycle
│   │   ├── CardMoba.ConfigService/
│   │   ├── CardMoba.Common/
│   │   └── CardMoba.DataAccess/    ← EF Core + Redis
│   ├── tests/
│   └── sql/init.sql                ← MySQL 8.0 schema
│
├── Config/                         ← Game config (Excel source → JSON export)
│   ├── Excel/
│   └── Json/{Cards,Heroes,Relics,Rules}/
│
├── Tools/                          ← .NET Core CLI tools
│   ├── ConfigTool/                 ← Config generation & validation
│   └── ExcelConverter/             ← Excel → JSON converter
│
└── Docs/
    ├── Design/                     ← Game design documents
    ├── Guides/                     ← Technical guides
    └── API/                        ← Protocol & API docs
```

### 1.3 Application Entry Point
- **Client entry**: `GameEntry` MonoBehaviour at `Client/Assets/Scripts/Common/GameEntry.cs`
  - Attached to root GameObject in the startup scene
  - `Awake()`: Calls `DontDestroyOnLoad`, initializes managers
  - `Start()`: Loads config, enters main menu
- **Server entry**: ASP.NET Core `Program.cs` in each service project (not yet created)
- **Shared**: Pure library, no entry point — consumed by both Client (via UPM) and Server (via ProjectReference)

### 1.4 Assembly Dependency Graph (ENFORCED by .asmdef)
```
Shared (noEngineReferences: true)
├── CardMoba.BattleCore    → refs: ConfigModels, Protocol
├── CardMoba.Protocol      → refs: (none)
└── CardMoba.ConfigModels  → refs: (none)

Client Assemblies:
├── CardMoba.Client.Common        → refs: (none)
├── CardMoba.Client.Network       → refs: Protocol
├── CardMoba.Client.Data          → refs: ConfigModels, Protocol, Client.Network
├── CardMoba.Client.GameLogic     → refs: BattleCore, ConfigModels, Protocol, Client.Data, Client.Network
├── CardMoba.Client.Presentation  → refs: ConfigModels, Client.GameLogic, Client.Data, Client.Common
└── CardMoba.Client.Editor        → refs: BattleCore, ConfigModels, Client.GameLogic, Client.Data, Client.Common [Editor-only]
```
**CRITICAL**: Dependencies flow DOWN only. Never add upward references (e.g., Network must NOT reference GameLogic).

