## 2. Code Style & Consistency Enforcers

### 2.1 Naming Conventions (C# Official + Project-Specific)
| Element | Convention | Example |
|---------|-----------|---------|
| Namespace | `CardMoba.{Layer}.{Module}` PascalCase | `CardMoba.Client.GameLogic.RoundFlow` |
| Class / Struct / Enum | PascalCase | `RoundStateMachine`, `CardTrackType` |
| Interface | `I` + PascalCase | `ISettlementHandler`, `ICardEffect` |
| Public method | PascalCase | `ProcessSettlement()`, `GetPlayerState()` |
| Public property | PascalCase | `PlayerId`, `CardName` |
| Public field | PascalCase | `TrackType`, `Cost` |
| Private field | `_` + camelCase | `_roundNumber`, `_playerStates` |
| Local variable | camelCase | `currentRound`, `targetPlayer` |
| Parameter | camelCase | `playerId`, `cardConfig` |
| Constant | PascalCase | `MaxHandSize`, `HeartbeatInterval` |
| Enum values | PascalCase (Chinese allowed for game-specific enums) | `瞬策牌 = 1`, `定策牌 = 2` |
| File name | Must match primary class name | `RoundStateMachine.cs` |
| asmdef name | `CardMoba.{Assembly}` | `CardMoba.Client.GameLogic.asmdef` |

### 2.2 Comment & Documentation Standards
- **Every** public class, method, property, and enum MUST have XML doc comments (`/// <summary>`)
- Core business logic and complex settlement code MUST have inline comments explaining the "why"
- Use `[Header("Section Name")]` attribute to group fields in MonoBehaviour / ScriptableObject inspectors
- Debug logs MUST use the format: `Debug.Log("[ModuleName] message")` — e.g., `Debug.Log("[CardSystem] 卡牌打出: " + cardId)`

### 2.3 File Structure Template (C# class)
```csharp
using UnityEngine;               // Unity namespaces first
using System;                    // System namespaces second
using System.Collections.Generic;
using CardMoba.BattleCore;       // Shared namespaces third
using CardMoba.Client.Data;      // Client namespaces fourth (respect layer order)

namespace CardMoba.Client.GameLogic.RoundFlow
{
    /// <summary>
    /// Brief description of the class purpose.
    /// </summary>
    public class ClassName : MonoBehaviour  // or plain class
    {
        // ── Serialized Fields ──
        [Header("配置")]
        [SerializeField] private int _configValue;

        // ── Private Fields ──
        private int _internalState;

        // ── Public Properties ──
        public int InternalState => _internalState;

        // ── Unity Lifecycle ──
        private void Awake() { }
        private void Start() { }
        private void OnDestroy() { }

        // ── Public Methods ──
        // ── Private Methods ──
    }
}
```

### 2.4 Formatting Rules
- Indentation: **4 spaces** (no tabs)
- Encoding: **UTF-8**
- Braces: Allman style (opening brace on new line for methods/classes)
- Max method length: **100 lines** — split into smaller methods if exceeded
- `using` statements: Ordered as Unity → System → Shared → Client (layered)

